      <li>22:00 - bed (8 hours of the fast were at work, and 8 were asleep)</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>My mood also seems much better this week, but that‚Äôs also because my work schedule has normalized and I‚Äôm getting out in the sun more (e.g. I was on swing shifts overnight the last few weeks).  I think, too, the ‚Äúcommunity‚Äù part of the challenge ‚Äì complimenting someone ‚Äì actually help my mood and makes me feel better regardless of how someone else takes it.  I‚Äôm definitely not one to brown-nose, so I‚Äôm not for superficial comments, the point is that you start to develop a <em>habit of seeking your own happiness.</em></li>
